Definition: lacking companions or companionship
Example: he was alone when we met him; she is alone much of the time; the lone skier on the mountain; a lonely fisherman stood on a tuft of gravel; a lonely soul; a solitary traveler
Synonyms: p, noun, attribute, aloneness, lone, a, lonely, state, loneliness, solitary, solitariness, lacking, companions, or, companionship, he, was, when, we, met, him, she, is, much, of, the, time, skier, on, mountain, fisherman, stood, tuft, gravel, soul, traveler
Category: adj.all
